column1: #Text=US Congressional panel claims Turkey committed genocide
#Text=A United States Congressional panel has passed a resolution describing Turkey 's killing of Armenians in World War I as genocide , over objections from the White House .
#Text=... characterise the systematic and deliberate annihilation of 1.5 million Armenians as genocide — Partial text of the resolution passed yesterday by the House Foreign Affairs Committee

#Text=The panel , the House Foreign Affairs Committee , passed the resolution , which calls on President Barack Obama to " characterize the systematic and deliberate annihilation of 1.5 million Armenians as genocide , " by a vote of 23 to 22 .

#Text=The passage came even after the White House warned the panel that the vote would harm talks between Turkey and Armenia , and US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton asked the panel not to proceed with the vote .
#Text=Additionally , a Turkish parliamentary delegation aimed at convincing panel members to defeat the resolution also had gone to Washington to plead their case .
#Text=Just minutes after the US resolution passed , Turkey issued a statement condemning " this resolution which accuses the Turkish nation of a crime it has not committed .
